1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,568
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:02,973
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:13,618 --> 00:00:14,677
Get in, 6835.

4
00:00:14,897 --> 00:00:16,254
No!

5
00:00:16,254 --> 00:00:17,659
No!

6
00:00:17,659 --> 00:00:18,659
No!

7
00:00:18,659 --> 00:00:20,458
No!

8
00:00:21,299 --> 00:00:22,493
No!

9
00:00:22,493 --> 00:00:23,928
(Episode 11)

10
00:00:29,138 --> 00:00:30,201
What a relief.

11
00:00:31,992 --> 00:00:33,304
Cho Eun Ae, you have a visitor.

12
00:00:34,164 --> 00:00:37,445
A visitor? Who?

13
00:00:38,306 --> 00:00:40,878
What did you just say? Intern?

14
00:00:41,059 --> 00:00:43,101
Yes, a six-month temporary position.

15
00:00:43,101 --> 00:00:46,017
An intern in Strategic Planning
at Kangsu Construction.

16
00:00:51,572 --> 00:00:52,572
You!

17
00:00:58,092 --> 00:00:59,730
Me?

18
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:01,232
Yes, you.

19
00:01:05,125 --> 00:01:06,771
Listen, Cho Eun Ae.

20
00:01:06,771 --> 00:01:08,449
Until recently,

21
00:01:08,449 --> 00:01:10,416
I was the co-CEO of Lucky Joy Tech.

22
00:01:10,664 --> 00:01:12,844
It was just a startup with two employees,

23
00:01:12,844 --> 00:01:14,579
but still,
I'm the one who developed Joy...

24
00:01:14,978 --> 00:01:17,148
with my own two hands. Joy is my baby.

25
00:01:17,148 --> 00:01:19,517
So, since you were a CEO,

26
00:01:19,517 --> 00:01:21,319
you're saying
being an intern makes no sense?

27
00:01:21,319 --> 00:01:22,992
No, that's not it.

28
00:01:23,629 --> 00:01:26,123
How could I possibly accept
being an intern...

29
00:01:26,123 --> 00:01:28,192
at Kangsu Construction,
the company that stole my program?

30
00:01:28,192 --> 00:01:29,193
Hold on.

31
00:01:29,193 --> 00:01:31,729
There's a major error
in what you're claiming.

32
00:01:31,892 --> 00:01:34,485
Kangsu Construction didn't steal Joy.

33
00:01:34,485 --> 00:01:37,122
It was
a completely legal acquisition transfer.

34
00:01:37,752 --> 00:01:39,952
That may be true on paper...

35
00:01:41,072 --> 00:01:43,674
But I didn't agree!

36
00:01:45,372 --> 00:01:46,532
From what I can see,

37
00:01:46,532 --> 00:01:49,514
you're not in a state to think rationally.

38
00:01:51,109 --> 00:01:52,825
If you don't accept my offer,

39
00:01:52,825 --> 00:01:54,966
Kangsu Construction
will proceed with a lawsuit immediately,

40
00:01:54,966 --> 00:01:56,451
without any settlement or leniency.

41
00:01:57,359 --> 00:01:59,457
This isn't an offer.
It's outright blackmail!

42
00:01:59,457 --> 00:02:01,592
Kangsu Construction won't let it slide
this time.

43
00:02:02,092 --> 00:02:04,328
The legal response team
has probably already been assembled.

44
00:02:04,992 --> 00:02:07,364
Given the scale of your crime,

45
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:10,101
you might even end up
with a life sentence.

46
00:02:10,878 --> 00:02:12,302
A life sentence?

47
00:02:12,764 --> 00:02:13,938
What are you...

48
00:02:16,325 --> 00:02:19,410
I heard you were caught on the spot
while taking photos of this.

49
00:02:20,104 --> 00:02:23,704
Did you really think
looking at this would help?

50
00:02:24,345 --> 00:02:25,345
Wait.

51
00:02:25,678 --> 00:02:27,978
Can I take a look at that document?

52
00:02:29,059 --> 00:02:30,154
Go ahead.

53
00:02:30,503 --> 00:02:32,656
You've ended up in detention
because of this.

54
00:02:32,656 --> 00:02:35,126
I suppose I can afford
that much generosity. Here.

55
00:02:36,859 --> 00:02:37,928
A little closer.

56
00:02:38,262 --> 00:02:39,563
Just a little more.

57
00:02:40,175 --> 00:02:42,267
A bit closer this way.

58
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:43,668
Lift it up a bit.

59
00:02:48,892 --> 00:02:50,107
Turn the page. Next.

60
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:53,244
Turn it, quickly.

61
00:02:55,746 --> 00:02:56,746
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

62
00:02:56,746 --> 00:02:58,549
(Warranty of Intellectual Property,
Basic Due Diligence)

63
00:02:58,549 --> 00:03:00,818
(Cooperation for Due Diligence,
Penalty for Breach)

64
00:03:00,818 --> 00:03:01,818
Next.

65
00:03:09,965 --> 00:03:11,998
How about giving that developer a chance?

66
00:03:12,451 --> 00:03:13,451
A chance?

67
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:16,067
Are you suggesting we recruit her?

68
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:18,130
It's not a bad idea.

69
00:03:18,359 --> 00:03:20,337
You already acknowledged
the program's excellence.

70
00:03:20,337 --> 00:03:22,297
You scouted one of the co-CEOs,

71
00:03:22,297 --> 00:03:24,542
so why not the other one as well?

72
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:26,985
That woman is completely unreasonable,
practically a psycho.

73
00:03:26,985 --> 00:03:28,645
We need to form teams anyway,

74
00:03:29,429 --> 00:03:32,709
so it's only fair
that both teams include a Joy developer.

75
00:03:32,709 --> 00:03:34,151
Well, that's true...

76
00:03:34,952 --> 00:03:36,790
But what if she causes
some kind of trouble?

77
00:03:37,951 --> 00:03:38,985
I'll...

78
00:03:40,772 --> 00:03:41,926
take responsibility.

79
00:03:47,032 --> 00:03:48,032
Hold on.

80
00:03:48,325 --> 00:03:52,125
"But anything other than Joy is excluded
from the contract,

81
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:54,638
and the specific items
shall be finalized...

82
00:03:54,638 --> 00:03:55,773
through separate specification
between the parties."

83
00:03:58,025 --> 00:03:59,477
There's no specification regarding...

84
00:03:59,477 --> 00:04:01,392
the memo embedded in the source code.

85
00:04:01,957 --> 00:04:03,447
You haven't finished reading it yet?

86
00:04:04,092 --> 00:04:05,092
What?

87
00:04:07,559 --> 00:04:08,886
I'm done reading it.

88
00:04:10,991 --> 00:04:13,658
You must've realized by now
that there's no way out.

89
00:04:15,459 --> 00:04:16,627
What are you going to do?

90
00:04:18,017 --> 00:04:20,759
- About what?
- Are you going to accept my offer...

91
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:22,925
or go to trial
and serve a prison sentence?

92
00:04:23,992 --> 00:04:25,825
I'll give you one day to think about it.

93
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:28,472
Is this how large corporations
always operate?

94
00:04:28,472 --> 00:04:30,741
How can you be so cold-blooded?

95
00:04:33,892 --> 00:04:37,114
Should a lion feel sorry
for eating a rabbit?

96
00:04:38,027 --> 00:04:39,648
This is a jungle.

97
00:04:40,659 --> 00:04:41,659
A jungle.

98
00:04:51,745 --> 00:04:52,745
Stay calm, Cho Eun Ae.

99
00:04:53,758 --> 00:04:54,958
It's not over yet.

100
00:05:02,745 --> 00:05:05,145
I told him not to hang
a shirt he's already worn inside.

101
00:05:07,578 --> 00:05:08,913
What is this smell?

102
00:05:16,925 --> 00:05:19,657
Honestly, is it that hard...

103
00:05:19,657 --> 00:05:21,058
to put the laundry in the laundry room?

104
00:05:25,863 --> 00:05:27,031
Look at this.

105
00:05:27,031 --> 00:05:30,539
She just left important documents
lying around like this.

106
00:05:36,485 --> 00:05:37,485
Hello?

107
00:05:38,678 --> 00:05:40,145
Kangsu Construction's PR team?

108
00:05:41,892 --> 00:05:43,748
You sent the promotional gift by email?

109
00:05:44,792 --> 00:05:46,450
Thank you.

110
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:50,891
Let's see.

111
00:05:56,225 --> 00:05:57,225
Excuse me.

112
00:05:57,844 --> 00:05:58,844
Yes?

113
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:02,325
I'd like to send some food to Cho Eun Ae.
How can I do that?

114
00:06:02,937 --> 00:06:04,768
You don't really need to do that.

115
00:06:04,768 --> 00:06:05,768
Sorry?

116
00:06:06,159 --> 00:06:08,416
She's eating well and sleeping well.

117
00:06:09,059 --> 00:06:10,741
Seems like she's perfectly suited
to a place like this.

118
00:06:11,904 --> 00:06:12,971
Is that so?

119
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:15,606
Eun Ae! Cho Eun Ae!

120
00:06:16,326 --> 00:06:18,382
Officer, where is Eun Ae?

121
00:06:18,718 --> 00:06:20,692
Where is my friend Cho Eun Ae?

122
00:06:20,692 --> 00:06:22,770
Please fill out
the application form first.

123
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:24,521
It's her first time in a place like this,

124
00:06:24,521 --> 00:06:27,091
so I brought some food
in case she hasn't been eating well.

125
00:06:27,092 --> 00:06:28,659
Bindaetteok, gimbap, tteokbokki.

126
00:06:28,659 --> 00:06:29,853
There are dumplings too.

127
00:06:29,853 --> 00:06:31,469
Can I go in and feed her this?

128
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:34,065
Outside food is not allowed.
Please take it back.

129
00:06:36,492 --> 00:06:37,676
Eun Ae!

130
00:06:38,102 --> 00:06:39,437
Cho Rong!

131
00:06:39,437 --> 00:06:41,944
- Eun Ae!
- Cho Rong!

132
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:44,041
How did this happen?

133
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:46,010
How did you end up in this cold...

134
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:48,125
I mean, in detention?

135
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:49,559
Trespassing.

136
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:52,649
You won't serve that long
just for trespassing.

137
00:06:52,649 --> 00:06:53,651
Property damage.

138
00:06:54,285 --> 00:06:56,587
Still, that's not too bad.

139
00:06:56,587 --> 00:06:58,892
Assault, violation
of the Unfair Competition Prevention Act,

140
00:06:58,892 --> 00:07:00,924
spreading false information,
attempted theft.

141
00:07:03,107 --> 00:07:04,695
Eun Ae.

142
00:07:04,695 --> 00:07:06,559
It might take you a while
to see sunlight again.

143
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:09,048
What are we going to do?

144
00:07:11,159 --> 00:07:13,270
The Bible, Buddhism...

145
00:07:13,692 --> 00:07:14,978
- Cheondoism.
- Cho Rong.

146
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:18,971
Are you telling me
to stay in detention forever?

147
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:20,597
Hey, what are you saying?

148
00:07:20,597 --> 00:07:24,459
Life outside means nothing to me
without you!

149
00:07:24,459 --> 00:07:27,725
Should I just commit a crime
and come in too?

150
00:07:27,725 --> 00:07:31,755
That's the only way I can stay with you.

151
00:07:31,755 --> 00:07:33,223
Cho Rong.

152
00:07:33,223 --> 00:07:35,566
Eun Ae.

153
00:07:37,838 --> 00:07:38,905
One minute remaining.

154
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:41,231
Wait a second!

155
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:45,536
(I tried not to cry,
but I can't hold back my tears.)

156
00:07:46,337 --> 00:07:50,164
(Thank you,
who else would cry like this for me?)

157
00:07:50,164 --> 00:07:51,164
(Until the day we meet again, eat well...)

158
00:07:51,164 --> 00:07:52,902
Visiting time is over. Please step out.

159
00:07:53,377 --> 00:07:55,992
(I'll be out soon.)

160
00:07:55,992 --> 00:07:57,481
Come on, step out.

161
00:07:58,582 --> 00:08:00,077
I'll go now.

162
00:08:00,077 --> 00:08:01,464
Eun Ae!

163
00:08:01,464 --> 00:08:02,919
Cho Rong.

164
00:08:02,919 --> 00:08:05,144
Cho Rong!

165
00:08:05,144 --> 00:08:06,687
Eun Ae!

166
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:14,131
I'm home.

167
00:08:14,323 --> 00:08:16,700
Where have you been,
wandering around until now?

168
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:17,892
You even skipped lunch.

169
00:08:17,892 --> 00:08:20,270
I'm not in any state to eat right now.

170
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,039
Eun Ae is in that cold...

171
00:08:23,985 --> 00:08:26,298
What is it? Did you hear from Eun Ae?

172
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:28,359
Sorry? No.

173
00:08:28,359 --> 00:08:31,259
You just said, "Eun Ae is...

174
00:08:32,217 --> 00:08:33,617
in that cold"...

175
00:08:34,772 --> 00:08:37,464
She rushed off to a seminar,

176
00:08:37,464 --> 00:08:39,124
so I figured
she didn't even bring proper clothes.

177
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:40,658
Maybe she caught a cold.

178
00:08:40,658 --> 00:08:43,194
She's tough as nails. She'll be fine.

179
00:08:43,692 --> 00:08:47,183
I'm starting line dancing next week.

180
00:08:48,459 --> 00:08:49,800
What did you say?

181
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,902
I said dancing.

182
00:08:52,302 --> 00:08:53,303
Line dancing.

183
00:08:53,303 --> 00:08:55,959
I filled out
a Kangsu Construction survey before,

184
00:08:55,959 --> 00:08:59,826
and they sent me a cultural center
class voucher as a free gift.

185
00:08:59,826 --> 00:09:01,412
If they're giving gifts,

186
00:09:01,412 --> 00:09:03,959
they should just send money
or a gift card.

187
00:09:04,939 --> 00:09:06,919
I've been feeling sluggish lately,

188
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:09,486
and I was thinking
of starting some exercise anyway.

189
00:09:10,751 --> 00:09:11,986
What should I do?

190
00:09:11,986 --> 00:09:13,625
She has no idea.

191
00:09:14,172 --> 00:09:16,539
Cho Rong,
why are you staring at me like that?

192
00:09:17,261 --> 00:09:18,829
Do you have something to tell me?

193
00:09:18,829 --> 00:09:20,864
Sorry? No.

194
00:09:21,251 --> 00:09:23,151
You just look especially beautiful today.

195
00:09:26,264 --> 00:09:27,599
By the way,

196
00:09:28,585 --> 00:09:31,765
what if you get carried away
with dancing...

197
00:09:32,858 --> 00:09:35,346
once you start that line dance thing?

198
00:09:36,173 --> 00:09:37,848
What do you mean carried away?

199
00:09:38,059 --> 00:09:40,717
Line dancing is exercise. It's a sport.

200
00:09:43,571 --> 00:09:44,788
Line dancing?

201
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:46,492
Look at me.

202
00:09:46,492 --> 00:09:49,163
Don't you think
my figure's gotten worse lately?

203
00:09:49,163 --> 00:09:52,676
If I let my guard down,
I'll never get back in shape.

204
00:09:52,676 --> 00:09:54,264
Let's do it together.

205
00:09:54,264 --> 00:09:57,522
You play golf all the time.
What more exercise do you need?

206
00:09:57,522 --> 00:10:00,402
Golf and dancing are completely different.

207
00:10:00,402 --> 00:10:01,772
Let's do it together.

208
00:10:02,085 --> 00:10:03,698
I even bought dance clothes and shoes...

209
00:10:03,698 --> 00:10:06,126
so we could do it together.

210
00:10:06,126 --> 00:10:07,311
Look.

211
00:10:07,859 --> 00:10:08,859
What?

212
00:10:09,359 --> 00:10:12,371
I've been feeling down lately
because of Father.

213
00:10:12,371 --> 00:10:14,451
I can't even laugh freely at home,

214
00:10:14,451 --> 00:10:16,553
and my husband comes home late every night
after drinking.

215
00:10:16,553 --> 00:10:18,776
Min Ho keeps telling me
to apologize to Seung Ri,

216
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:21,258
pouring ice water
over himself every night.

217
00:10:21,959 --> 00:10:25,162
Min Ho poured ice water over himself?

218
00:10:25,162 --> 00:10:27,559
Yeah, until I apologized.

219
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:30,134
He said
it was some kind of self-punishment.

220
00:10:30,701 --> 00:10:32,002
No wonder.

221
00:10:32,464 --> 00:10:34,631
I thought it was strange
since you're not the type...

222
00:10:35,011 --> 00:10:36,507
to come apologize in person.

223
00:10:36,507 --> 00:10:39,025
Anyway, we're doing it together, okay?

224
00:10:45,292 --> 00:10:46,683
Have you been well, Chairman?

225
00:10:47,092 --> 00:10:49,086
I didn't want to wake you,
so I couldn't greet you earlier.

226
00:10:50,032 --> 00:10:51,232
It's been a while.

227
00:10:51,792 --> 00:10:55,037
You always send things for this old man,

228
00:10:55,878 --> 00:10:57,161
yet I'm only thanking you now.

229
00:10:57,651 --> 00:10:59,344
Not at all.

230
00:10:59,696 --> 00:11:01,526
Compared to what I owe you,

231
00:11:01,758 --> 00:11:04,068
I feel like I've done nothing.
I'm just grateful.

232
00:11:04,935 --> 00:11:08,038
The kimchi you sent was delicious, madam.

233
00:11:08,038 --> 00:11:09,625
Welcome, Jeong Ran.

234
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:12,159
Are you two heading out? A date?

235
00:11:13,258 --> 00:11:14,644
A date?

236
00:11:15,072 --> 00:11:16,405
We'll be back soon.

237
00:11:17,465 --> 00:11:19,632
Then take your time and enjoy yourselves.

238
00:11:21,038 --> 00:11:22,538
Let's go, Ms. Lee Yeong Hwa.

239
00:11:23,065 --> 00:11:24,421
Sorry?

240
00:11:26,292 --> 00:11:29,511
Go on ahead, Ms. Lee Yeong Hwa.

241
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:43,774
Father feels like a different person
these days.

242
00:11:43,775 --> 00:11:46,710
He's so affectionate
it gives me goosebumps.

243
00:11:47,292 --> 00:11:49,246
Why? It's nice to see him like that.

244
00:11:49,758 --> 00:11:52,094
I understand how he feels.

245
00:11:52,925 --> 00:11:54,785
Dae Chi being devoted...

246
00:11:55,038 --> 00:11:56,854
must run in the family.

247
00:11:57,498 --> 00:12:00,198
You think that's always a good thing?
It's not.

248
00:12:00,426 --> 00:12:02,666
- Why not?
- Out of Father's shares,

249
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:04,224
maybe 20 percent could just vanish.

250
00:12:04,825 --> 00:12:05,891
Never mind.

251
00:12:06,259 --> 00:12:07,792
Nothing's certain yet.

252
00:12:12,292 --> 00:12:14,744
What? The Philosophy Department
is shutting down?

253
00:12:15,925 --> 00:12:18,275
So you're saying you'll be unemployed?

254
00:12:18,991 --> 00:12:20,191
Unemployed?

255
00:12:20,191 --> 00:12:22,092
Isn't that a bit extreme?

256
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:25,782
I've already applied to the school
the department head recommended,

257
00:12:25,782 --> 00:12:27,117
and I'm waiting for the results.

258
00:12:28,292 --> 00:12:30,138
Is that why you stayed out that night?

259
00:12:32,158 --> 00:12:33,657
My situation is a problem,

260
00:12:34,451 --> 00:12:36,426
but I'm more worried
about the current reality.

261
00:12:37,185 --> 00:12:39,563
Philosophy is the foundation
and essence of all studies,

262
00:12:39,563 --> 00:12:41,792
and if it gets shut down
just because it doesn't lead to jobs...

263
00:12:41,792 --> 00:12:44,059
The whole education system will collapse?

264
00:12:44,059 --> 00:12:46,712
- Yeah.
- Our family will collapse first!

265
00:12:47,118 --> 00:12:49,413
Right now, we have kindergarten fees,
living expenses, health insurance,

266
00:12:49,413 --> 00:12:51,288
education insurance, utilities, savings...

267
00:12:51,675 --> 00:12:53,977
Do you know how much we spend every month?

268
00:12:53,977 --> 00:12:55,825
Why would our family collapse?

269
00:12:56,425 --> 00:12:58,515
Don't worry too much, honey.

270
00:12:58,803 --> 00:13:00,730
Can you trust me and wait a little longer?

271
00:13:01,278 --> 00:13:03,387
How long should I wait, exactly?

272
00:13:03,959 --> 00:13:05,255
How can we ever buy a house...

273
00:13:05,255 --> 00:13:08,191
and live like everyone else
with just my salary?

274
00:13:11,066 --> 00:13:12,863
Are you fighting again, Mom and Dad?

275
00:13:12,863 --> 00:13:14,598
No, we're not fighting.

276
00:13:15,659 --> 00:13:18,535
If it's about money, I can help.

277
00:13:19,169 --> 00:13:20,337
- What?
- What?

278
00:13:20,337 --> 00:13:22,339
I have a lot of money in my piggy bank.

279
00:13:22,738 --> 00:13:25,571
And I won't go to kindergarten
starting tomorrow.

280
00:13:26,012 --> 00:13:29,513
I'll eat less and won't ask for snacks.

281
00:13:30,248 --> 00:13:31,815
Bit Na.

282
00:13:33,292 --> 00:13:34,292
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

283
00:13:35,446 --> 00:13:38,779
I promise Mom and Dad won't fight anymore.

284
00:13:39,158 --> 00:13:40,158
Okay!

285
00:13:41,812 --> 00:13:42,812
Then make up.

286
00:13:43,277 --> 00:13:44,477
- Okay.
- Okay.

287
00:13:49,032 --> 00:13:50,867
(Kangsu Construction)

288
00:14:03,332 --> 00:14:04,332
Seong Jun.

289
00:14:05,938 --> 00:14:07,138
Do you have a moment to talk?

290
00:14:07,625 --> 00:14:08,725
Sure, go ahead.

291
00:14:09,912 --> 00:14:12,122
Don't misunderstand. Try applying here.

292
00:14:15,992 --> 00:14:18,092
It's someone I knew
when I was running my business,

293
00:14:18,092 --> 00:14:19,396
and he's trustworthy.

294
00:14:19,925 --> 00:14:21,992
It's a small company, but it's solid.

295
00:14:23,925 --> 00:14:24,992
I want you to find work that suits you,

296
00:14:25,672 --> 00:14:28,205
where you can really show your abilities.

297
00:14:29,492 --> 00:14:30,807
Thanks for looking out for me.

298
00:14:31,365 --> 00:14:32,743
I've already put in a word,

299
00:14:33,252 --> 00:14:35,485
so if you submit your resume,
you'll probably get an interview.

300
00:14:36,092 --> 00:14:39,983
Okay, if I get the job,
let's have a drink sometime.

301
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:42,958
By the way, Gwon Sik...

302
00:14:44,638 --> 00:14:45,989
I...

303
00:14:48,831 --> 00:14:50,452
Team Manager Ko.

304
00:14:57,892 --> 00:14:59,625
- This is...
- I know him.

305
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:02,191
Dae Chi introduced us before.

306
00:15:03,065 --> 00:15:04,468
Did he?

307
00:15:08,292 --> 00:15:09,292
Yes, Chairman.

308
00:15:11,072 --> 00:15:12,315
I'll report to you right away.

309
00:15:15,051 --> 00:15:16,151
You're busy, so go on.

310
00:15:16,151 --> 00:15:17,151
Please head in, Mr. Seo.

311
00:15:17,699 --> 00:15:19,332
- I'll be off.
- Bye.

312
00:15:24,325 --> 00:15:26,125
I have something to say.

313
00:15:27,359 --> 00:15:29,459
I just came from seeing Cho Eun Ae.

314
00:15:29,665 --> 00:15:30,665
Sorry?

315
00:15:31,105 --> 00:15:33,572
I made her an offer,

316
00:15:34,039 --> 00:15:35,472
and I need you to persuade her.

317
00:15:36,351 --> 00:15:37,351
Persuade her?

318
00:15:40,111 --> 00:15:42,098
I didn't order makgeolli.

319
00:15:43,314 --> 00:15:44,748
It's on the house.

320
00:15:44,992 --> 00:15:47,192
You're not just passersby.

321
00:15:48,125 --> 00:15:49,486
Well, my wife...

322
00:15:50,205 --> 00:15:52,372
I mentioned traditional bindaetteok once,

323
00:15:53,292 --> 00:15:54,692
and she tracked down this place.

324
00:15:55,705 --> 00:15:57,285
Look at that millstone.

325
00:15:58,097 --> 00:16:00,530
You don't see that much these days.

326
00:16:00,865 --> 00:16:04,018
Seems like your husband doesn't know...

327
00:16:04,018 --> 00:16:07,237
how amazing our Joy is.

328
00:16:07,859 --> 00:16:10,040
Sorry? Joy?

329
00:16:11,685 --> 00:16:13,119
I'll tell you about it.

330
00:16:13,119 --> 00:16:15,180
Eat this before it gets cold.

331
00:16:25,959 --> 00:16:26,959
This is really...

332
00:16:27,792 --> 00:16:28,892
This is the real deal.

333
00:16:29,351 --> 00:16:31,403
Right? It's the real deal.

334
00:16:32,752 --> 00:16:33,952
Please enjoy.

335
00:16:38,101 --> 00:16:40,834
How did you find this place?

336
00:16:41,465 --> 00:16:42,778
And what is Joy?

337
00:16:42,778 --> 00:16:44,445
Actually,

338
00:16:45,232 --> 00:16:49,580
I stopped by there not long ago,
where that restaurant used to be.

339
00:16:54,659 --> 00:16:58,310
I was just passing by
and decided to drop in.

340
00:16:59,364 --> 00:17:02,859
And that's where I met a young lady.

341
00:17:04,260 --> 00:17:06,593
I'm just stepping out for a bit.

342
00:17:06,593 --> 00:17:09,426
Take your time and enjoy your food.

343
00:17:12,525 --> 00:17:15,792
Tomorrow at two? I'll see you then.

344
00:17:18,631 --> 00:17:21,397
Why did you come?
Those customers just went in.

345
00:17:23,747 --> 00:17:27,050
That old couple was all lovey-dovey,

346
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:30,820
so I stepped out
to give them some privacy.

347
00:17:31,938 --> 00:17:32,938
I see.

348
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:35,678
Well,

349
00:17:36,192 --> 00:17:39,830
if someone who never wears perfume
suddenly smells like it,

350
00:17:40,099 --> 00:17:43,033
what would you think?

351
00:17:43,732 --> 00:17:45,732
Your husband was wearing perfume?

352
00:17:45,911 --> 00:17:48,011
No, it's just that a customer I know...

353
00:17:48,524 --> 00:17:50,580
said her husband's clothes...

354
00:17:50,894 --> 00:17:53,176
suddenly smelled like perfume
when they never had before.

355
00:17:53,744 --> 00:17:54,744
He's having an affair.

356
00:17:56,052 --> 00:17:57,452
An affair?

357
00:17:57,959 --> 00:17:59,883
No, he's not the type.

358
00:17:59,883 --> 00:18:02,052
I don't think he is either.

359
00:18:03,759 --> 00:18:06,588
Don't suffer alone. Just ask him directly.

360
00:18:07,559 --> 00:18:09,492
I told you it's not my husband.

361
00:18:09,825 --> 00:18:11,408
I, Park Sun Bun,

362
00:18:11,962 --> 00:18:15,425
can see through a millstone.

363
00:18:18,251 --> 00:18:21,251
If everything other than Joy is excluded
from the contract,

364
00:18:21,959 --> 00:18:24,425
then the blind date app
and counseling app in development,

365
00:18:24,992 --> 00:18:27,860
as well as the people-finding annotations
and idea memos,

366
00:18:27,860 --> 00:18:30,146
are all non-transferable items, right?

367
00:18:32,218 --> 00:18:33,652
In that case...

368
00:18:33,652 --> 00:18:35,952
Kangsu Construction won't let this slide
this time.

369
00:18:36,325 --> 00:18:38,655
The legal response team
has probably already been assembled.

370
00:18:39,425 --> 00:18:41,758
Given the scale of your wrongdoing,

371
00:18:42,192 --> 00:18:44,359
you might even end up
with a life sentence.

372
00:18:46,158 --> 00:18:49,191
So that slick punk thought
I'd be easy to push around?

373
00:18:50,359 --> 00:18:52,192
I've made up my mind.

374
00:18:52,525 --> 00:18:54,286
Cho Eun Ae, you have a visitor.

375
00:18:56,225 --> 00:18:59,209
That slick team manager
wants you to convince me...

376
00:18:59,544 --> 00:19:00,744
to accept the intern offer?

377
00:19:01,525 --> 00:19:04,514
Yes. That's the best option for now.

378
00:19:05,192 --> 00:19:07,117
I heard the CPO approved it too.

379
00:19:08,959 --> 00:19:10,353
Fine, I'll accept it.

380
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:12,889
Really? Do you mean it?

381
00:19:13,892 --> 00:19:16,192
Take two steps back
to move one step forward.

382
00:19:16,859 --> 00:19:18,194
You said you trusted me, right?

383
00:19:19,131 --> 00:19:21,364
Of course I trust you.

384
00:19:23,211 --> 00:19:26,235
But didn't Mom get suspicious or anything?

385
00:19:26,925 --> 00:19:29,572
Please make sure Mom doesn't catch on,
Dad.

386
00:19:30,709 --> 00:19:33,109
Okay, don't worry.

387
00:19:38,059 --> 00:19:40,992
Will she say this smells
like disinfectant?

388
00:19:49,938 --> 00:19:51,604
Honey, dinner's ready.

389
00:19:53,365 --> 00:19:54,764
What is that smell?

390
00:19:56,292 --> 00:19:57,292
Smell?

391
00:19:58,145 --> 00:19:59,845
What smell? I don't smell anything.

392
00:20:00,712 --> 00:20:01,778
Come out already.

393
00:20:02,525 --> 00:20:03,525
Okay.

394
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:21,291
Mom, why have you been looking at Dad
like that?

395
00:20:22,592 --> 00:20:23,592
Like what?

396
00:20:24,045 --> 00:20:27,445
Like a starving hyena
that just spotted a baby goat.

397
00:20:35,486 --> 00:20:37,474
Go ahead and eat. I need to make a call.

398
00:20:42,358 --> 00:20:43,758
Why? What's wrong, Mom?

399
00:20:44,659 --> 00:20:46,625
Then, when will she be released?

400
00:20:48,325 --> 00:20:51,657
Okay, then I'll go tomorrow morning.

401
00:20:55,325 --> 00:20:56,593
Who's being released?

402
00:20:57,324 --> 00:20:58,324
What?

403
00:20:58,324 --> 00:21:00,930
You said someone's getting out
tomorrow morning and that you're going.

404
00:21:01,270 --> 00:21:03,310
What place would I be going to
in the morning?

405
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,401
It's obviously the office.

406
00:21:07,892 --> 00:21:10,173
This is suspicious.
There's definitely something going on.

407
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:13,343
Yes, Mr. Hwang. Understood.

408
00:21:14,925 --> 00:21:15,925
How did it go?

409
00:21:15,925 --> 00:21:17,125
She'll be released tomorrow morning.

410
00:21:17,759 --> 00:21:20,750
Looks like it'll take some time
doing this and that.

411
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,925
That's a relief. She accepted the offer
without much resistance.

412
00:21:23,605 --> 00:21:25,505
She didn't have much choice
if she didn't want a criminal record.

413
00:21:26,592 --> 00:21:29,859
Can you really take responsibility
like you said, Team Manager Ko?

414
00:21:29,859 --> 00:21:33,230
Of course. Then I'll head out for the day.

415
00:21:34,959 --> 00:21:35,959
I should get going too.

416
00:21:36,659 --> 00:21:37,925
Just a moment, Ms. Seo.

417
00:21:39,892 --> 00:21:42,426
Thank you for accepting
my mother's apology.

418
00:21:42,924 --> 00:21:44,124
Which is why...

419
00:21:45,712 --> 00:21:47,745
Never mind.
I'm sure you already have plans.

420
00:21:49,792 --> 00:21:52,615
Would you like to have dinner together
if you're free?

421
00:21:53,338 --> 00:21:55,685
What? Yeah.

422
00:22:00,123 --> 00:22:03,504
I mean, you know how in books or dramas,

423
00:22:03,758 --> 00:22:06,158
people always say,
"Is this a dream or real life?"

424
00:22:06,959 --> 00:22:08,331
That's exactly how I feel right now.

425
00:22:09,092 --> 00:22:10,525
But what brought this on?
You actually asked me...

426
00:22:10,525 --> 00:22:11,901
to have dinner first.

427
00:22:11,901 --> 00:22:13,536
What did you do to your mother?

428
00:22:13,904 --> 00:22:15,738
She's not someone who apologizes easily.

429
00:22:16,525 --> 00:22:20,109
I just did to me what she did to you...

430
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:23,246
No, actually, maybe ten times more?

431
00:22:24,345 --> 00:22:25,812
- What?
- It was something like that.

432
00:22:26,259 --> 00:22:27,259
You should eat.

433
00:22:29,292 --> 00:22:31,459
Actually, I have a favor to ask, Chief Ko.

434
00:22:31,792 --> 00:22:33,656
A favor? Just say the word.

435
00:22:34,025 --> 00:22:36,459
If it's for you, I'll do anything.

436
00:22:36,625 --> 00:22:38,361
The teams haven't been finalized yet,

437
00:22:39,058 --> 00:22:40,525
so please assign me to Team Two.

438
00:22:43,478 --> 00:22:44,478
What?

439
00:22:48,459 --> 00:22:51,107
That's why you asked me out to dinner?

440
00:22:51,559 --> 00:22:55,378
Yes.
I know the team manager decides the team,

441
00:22:55,719 --> 00:22:58,886
but please respect the members' wishes,
Chief Ko.

442
00:23:02,318 --> 00:23:03,553
(Story World Community)

443
00:23:03,553 --> 00:23:04,819
(Online: Napkin Genius, Oh My Oz)

444
00:23:04,819 --> 00:23:05,825
Napkin Genius?

445
00:23:08,058 --> 00:23:10,191
That's the ID that always leaves
the first comment on my novel.

446
00:23:13,730 --> 00:23:15,563
(Oh My Oz messaging Napkin Genius)

447
00:23:18,935 --> 00:23:19,935
(Story World Community)

448
00:23:19,935 --> 00:23:21,070
(New Message,
You have a message from Oh My Oz.)

449
00:23:24,492 --> 00:23:25,492
What?

450
00:23:25,825 --> 00:23:29,979
Napkin Genius, aren't you
a huge fan of "The ER Witch?"

451
00:23:30,258 --> 00:23:33,283
Yes, I am. Do you know me?

452
00:23:35,492 --> 00:23:36,653
I'm a fan too.

453
00:23:37,652 --> 00:23:40,780
A fan of "The ER Witch?"
You really know good writing.

454
00:23:41,658 --> 00:23:45,996
I actually think
the author might be a genius doctor.

455
00:23:47,064 --> 00:23:49,532
Why do you think that?

456
00:23:50,592 --> 00:23:52,936
The realism is no joke,

457
00:23:52,936 --> 00:23:55,105
and the exaggeration makes
martial arts novels look tame.

458
00:23:56,292 --> 00:23:57,740
It's a full-on hero narrative.

459
00:23:58,125 --> 00:24:01,411
Napkin Genius,
you seem to have a very discerning eye.

460
00:24:01,964 --> 00:24:04,895
If you don't mind me asking,
what do you do?

461
00:24:09,218 --> 00:24:11,451
I'm an artist.

462
00:24:11,859 --> 00:24:12,859
An artist?

463
00:24:14,725 --> 00:24:16,092
What kind of genre?

464
00:24:16,579 --> 00:24:17,859
No comment for now.

465
00:24:18,792 --> 00:24:21,983
Someday, the whole world will be buzzing.

466
00:24:24,025 --> 00:24:26,943
Recently, some creepy psycho...

467
00:24:26,943 --> 00:24:29,325
calling himself an artist
really brought me down.

468
00:24:30,340 --> 00:24:32,909
But chatting with you today
about the work we both love...

469
00:24:32,909 --> 00:24:35,044
has really lifted my spirits.

470
00:24:36,212 --> 00:24:38,858
I ran into some crazy girl
not long ago too.

471
00:24:39,959 --> 00:24:42,112
I kind of want to set
that artist jerk up...

472
00:24:42,325 --> 00:24:43,753
with that crazy girl.

473
00:24:45,625 --> 00:24:47,857
A creepy psycho and a crazy girl?

474
00:24:48,192 --> 00:24:49,792
They sound like a perfect match.

475
00:24:56,825 --> 00:24:59,252
Hey, Min Ho's still not home yet?

476
00:24:59,252 --> 00:25:00,837
No, not yet. Why?

477
00:25:03,669 --> 00:25:04,674
You're late, son.

478
00:25:04,674 --> 00:25:06,363
Come with me. We need to talk.

479
00:25:08,046 --> 00:25:09,379
What kind of trouble did you get into?

480
00:25:15,892 --> 00:25:17,092
What's with them?

481
00:25:17,625 --> 00:25:20,023
Why does it have to be
the two men I love most in the world?

482
00:25:24,259 --> 00:25:26,692
How did it go? Did you resolve it?

483
00:25:27,025 --> 00:25:29,065
Yes, she'll be released tomorrow morning.

484
00:25:29,065 --> 00:25:31,367
Did you make sure it was handled cleanly
so there won't be any more issues?

485
00:25:31,525 --> 00:25:32,959
Gyeol said he'd take responsibility.

486
00:25:32,959 --> 00:25:35,171
Gyeol? What responsibility, and how?

487
00:25:35,307 --> 00:25:37,340
Please just trust me and let me do my job!

488
00:25:38,174 --> 00:25:39,606
If this gets any louder,

489
00:25:39,606 --> 00:25:41,611
before the race even starts, Gyeol...

490
00:25:41,611 --> 00:25:43,045
I won't lose. Never!

491
00:25:44,460 --> 00:25:47,050
Don't just talk. Show me!

492
00:26:03,885 --> 00:26:06,202
There's definitely someone
in his swimming class.

493
00:26:07,132 --> 00:26:09,266
I'm going to find out today,
no matter what.

494
00:26:13,759 --> 00:26:14,759
Dad.

495
00:26:16,525 --> 00:26:17,525
Eun Ae.

496
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:22,819
You've been through a lot, my daughter.

497
00:26:23,852 --> 00:26:25,021
I'm sorry, Dad.

498
00:26:27,559 --> 00:26:30,560
It's okay.
What matters is that you're out now.

499
00:26:32,425 --> 00:26:33,552
Eat this.

500
00:26:33,998 --> 00:26:36,466
If you eat this, you'll never come back
to a place like this.

501
00:26:40,158 --> 00:26:42,431
Cho Seong Jun, Cho Eun Ae.

502
00:26:43,974 --> 00:26:44,974
Honey...

503
00:26:47,218 --> 00:26:48,937
- Honey.
- Mom.

504
00:27:11,467 --> 00:27:14,470
(Our Happy Days)

505
00:27:14,804 --> 00:27:17,258
From now on,
I will live one day at a time.

506
00:27:17,258 --> 00:27:20,085
Stop joking, and tell me the real reason.

507
00:27:20,085 --> 00:27:21,444
Why did you change your mind?

508
00:27:21,444 --> 00:27:23,179
Start over?

509
00:27:23,179 --> 00:27:24,447
Hadn't you already given up?

510
00:27:24,447 --> 00:27:26,149
This is the last time.

511
00:27:26,382 --> 00:27:28,857
Before I die,
I absolutely have to find her.

512
00:27:29,085 --> 00:27:30,386
How amazing must it have been...

513
00:27:30,386 --> 00:27:32,104
for them to make the scouting offer first?

514
00:27:32,104 --> 00:27:34,457
Keep your mouth shut for the time being.

515
00:27:34,457 --> 00:27:36,659
I can be disappointed in my children,

516
00:27:36,659 --> 00:27:39,011
but I will not tolerate
you disappointing me.

517
00:27:39,359 --> 00:27:40,637
What? Fake employment?

518
00:27:40,637 --> 00:27:42,365
You're saying you'll join
as an intern first...

519
00:27:42,365 --> 00:27:44,167
and then bring those back out?

520
00:27:44,167 --> 00:27:45,832
I'll pull everything out within a month...

521
00:27:45,832 --> 00:27:46,836
and get back on my feet.

522
00:27:46,836 --> 00:27:47,870
Just watch.

523
00:27:47,870 --> 00:27:49,325
Watch how I rise again.

524
00:27:49,505 --> 00:27:51,207
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
